{
  "text": "Control -sham-exposed mice; 10 x 0.01 Gy -mice exposed to ten fractions of 0.01 Gy X-rays; 10 x 0.02 Gy -mice exposed to ten fractions of 0.02 Gy X-rays; 10 x 0.1 Gy -mice exposed to ten fractions of 0.1 Gy X-rays. Mean values obtained from two independent experiments are presented; in each experiment experimental groups consisted of 24 mice each. *indicates statistically significant (p<0.05) difference from the control group. than the same tissue in C57BL/6 mice [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Moreover, cells from radiosensitive, cancer-prone BALB/c mice showed inefficient non-homologous end joining of the γray-induced double-strand breaks as compared with cells from the C57BL/6 and other commonly used strains of mice [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
